title: Represents a Fundamental message. See Fundamental Message Format

Symbol.title: The Symbol ID to match with watch request.

ExchangeID.title: This is the Exchange Group ID.

AverageVolume.title: Average daily volume in 1000's of shares (4 week average).

52WeekHigh.title: Highest price of the last 52 weeks. For futures, this is the contract High.

52WeekLow.title: Lowest price of the last 52 weeks. For futures, this is the contract Low.

CalendarYearHigh.title: High price for the current calendar year.

CalendarYearLow.title: Low price for the current calendar year.

DividendYield.title: The annual dividends per share paid by the company divided by the current market price per share of stock sent as a percentage.

DividendRate.title: The annualized amount at which a dividend is expected to be paid by a company.

PayDate.title: Date on which a company made its last dividend payment.

ExDividendDate.title: The actual date in which a stock goes ex-dividend, typically about 3 weeks before the dividend is paid to shareholders of record. Also the amount of the dividend is reflected in a reduction of the share price on this date.

CurrentYearEarningsPerShare.title: The portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock.

NextYearEarningsPerShare.title: The total amount of earnings per share a company is estimated to accumulate over the next four quarters of the current fiscal year.

FiveYearGrowthPercentage.title: Earnings Per Share growth rate over a five year period.

FiscalYearEnd.title: The two digit month that the fiscal year ends for a company.

PercentHeldByInstitutions.title: A percentage of outstanding shares held by banks and institutions.

Beta.title: A coefficient measuring a stock's relative volatility. It is the covariance of a stock in relation to the rest of the stock market. 30 day historical volatility.

CurrentAssets.title: The amount of total current assets held by a company as of a specific date in Millions (lastADate).

CurrentLiabilities.title: The amount of total current liabilities held by a company as of a specific date in Millions (lastADate).

BalanceSheetDate.title: Last date that a company issued their quarterly report.

LongTermDebt.title: The amount of long term debt held by a company as of a specific date in Millions(lastADate).

CommonSharesOutstanding.title: The amount of common shares outstanding in 1000's of shares.

FormatCode.title: Display format code, See: Price Format Codes.

SIC.title: Federally designed numbering system identifying companies by industry. This 4 digit number corresponds to a specific industry.

HistoricalVolatility.title: 30-trading day volatility that it is calculated using Black-Scholes model. NOTE: For futures symbols this field is the Implied Volatility instead of Historical Volatility.

SecurityType.title: The security type code, See: Security Types.

ListedMarket.title: The listing market ID, See: Listed Markets.

52WeekHighDate.title: The date of the highest price of the last 52 weeks. For futures, this is the contract High Date.

52WeekLowDate.title: The date of the lowest price of the last 52 weeks. For futures, this is the contract Low Date.

CalendarYearHighDate.title: Date at which the High price for the current calendar year occurred.

CalendarYearLowDate.title: Date at which the Low price for the current calendar year occurred.

YearEndClose.title: Price of Year End Close. (Equities Only).

MaturityDate.title: Date of maturity for a Bond.

ExpirationDate.title: IEOptions, Futures, FutureOptions, and SSFutures only.

ExchangeRoot.title: The root symbol that you can find this symbol listed under at the exchange.

ContractSize.title: Deliverable quantity of a future or option contract.

ContractMonths.title: non-delimited string of upper-case single character month codes.

SecuritySubType.title: The security SubType code, See: Security Sub-Types.
